About Us
Sherwood's History
Sherwood's was opened in 1968 to serve the Jacksonville area quality drinks in a fun and inviting environment. We are family owned an operated by three generations of locals who take pride in the love they have for "Duvaaalll" and all its people.
Location
We are conveniently located right where the hustle of downtown Jacksonville meets the historic San Marco neighborhood. Our long-time bar is hard to miss, that is thanks to our stunningly intricate mural done by a well-known local artist Jason Tetlak. You'll find us just beyond the overpass by the train tracks, just look for the mural!
Services, Games, & More!
Not only do we offer multiple pool tables and dart boards, but pin ball, virtual golf and bowling as well! In our back bar, The Stable, we have beer pong, life-sized jenga and checkers for all to enjoy. Our touch tunes music system allows for our patrons to pick what they want to hear while they enjoy their cocktail of choice.
